Bradshaw, seated as President; Cromwell, Ireton, 
              Harrison, Downes, Marten, Tichburne, and other Judges on benches;
              Cook, and other Lawyers, Clerks, &c., at a table; a chair of State for the
              King on one side; the Queen, veiled, and other Ladies in a Gallery behind; 
              the whole stage filled with Guards Spectators, &c., &c.
